<HEADLINE>
<P>
POPE AGAIN APPEALS FOR PEACE IN LEBANON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VATICAN CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pope John Paul II again appealed for peace in Lebanon in a Christmas message to 
the spiritual leader of the war-torn nation's Maronite Christian community. 
</P>
<P>
"May God prosper the efforts of all those . . . seeking a just solution to the 
grave problems which delay the return to normality greatly desired by all 
Lebanese," the Pope said in a letter to Maronite Christian Patriarch Nasrallah 
Pierre Sfeir. The text was released by the Vatican on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
