<P>
TALKS BEGIN ON UNITING TWO YEMEN COUNTRIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANA, Yemen 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Yemeni leader Ali Salim Bidh arrived in Yemen on Sunday to pursue 
negotiations on a plan to unify the two states. 
</P>
<P>
Bidh, secretary general of the ruling Socialist Party, told the Yemeni news 
agency SABA that the atmosphere since the two Yemens signed a draft unity 
constitution three weeks ago has been good. 
</P>
<P>
He said the purpose of his talks with Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh will 
be to ensure that the agreement is implemented. 
</P>
<P>
Since the two Yemens signed the draft constitution, to be referred to their 
legislative bodies for endorsement, they have pulled back troops from border 
areas. 
</P>
