<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN IS ARRESTED IN KIDNAPING AND RAPE OF TEEN-AGE JOB-SEEKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An East Los Angeles man was in jail Sunday for investigation of kidnaping a 
16-year old girl on the pretense of finding her a job. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles police said Frank Palomino, 37, was arrested Saturday after his 
alleged victim spotted him in another car as detectives were returning her to 
the city from Tijuana. 
</P>
<P>
Hollenbeck Division Detective John Santy said Palomino, on Thursday, told the 
girl and her aunt that he would take them to places where they could find jobs. 
He dropped the aunt off at one location and then sped off with the girl to 
Tijuana. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators allege the suspect raped her in a motel room and held her there 
against her will. Despite the presence of another man who was guarding the 
motel room, the girl -- who had come to the United States from her native 
Mexico two months ago -- was able to escape and summon help, Santy said. 
</P>
<P>
After being alerted by Tijuana authorities, two Los Angeles detectives went to 
Tijuana to return her to Los Angeles for questioning, Santy said. As they were 
driving back on Interstate 5, the girl spotted Palomino driving alongside them. 
The detectives pulled the car over and took Palmonio into custody. 
</P>
<P>
He was being held in lieu of $7,500 bail at Parker Center Jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
