danger of the ideas getting watered down. For a work in a public space to be 
successful, it's absolutely necessary for it to maintain its strength and 
integrity. At the same time, the artist must acknowledge the needs of the 
situation." -- Mary Miss, New York sculptor, in ARTnews 
