<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIEL CERONE and SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'911' to the Rescue: Glenn and Annie Murphy of St. Louis saved the lives of 
their children as a result of watching an installment of CBS' "Rescue 911" in 
Annie Murphy's hospital room. Annie Murphy, under observation for a mysterious 
illness, was watching the show when the couple realized her symptoms mirrored 
those of an elderly woman who had become ill from a gas leak at her home. Glenn 
Murphy rushed home to find three children unconscious and one disoriented; he 
rushed them to the hospital and all family members have recovered. DANIEL 
CERONE and SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
