<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SLAIN MAN FOUND AT PICNIC GROUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man was found shot to death Saturday at the Pyramid Lake picnic 
grounds, the Los Angeles sheriff's department reported. 
</P>
<P>
The man, who was in sitting position against a wall separating the picnic area 
from a parking lot, was found about 3:15 p.m. by a group of fishermen, said 
Sheriff's Sgt. Bruce Sonnenblick. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities at first thought the man, age 35 to 40, had died of natural causes. 
But a coroner's deputy later found a single bullet wound in his chest, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The body was fully clothed. Homicide detectives are investigating, said 
Sonnenblick. 
</P>
</TEXT>
