<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BODY DISCOVERED NEAR FREEWAY OFF-RAMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An off-duty Los Angeles sheriff's deputy Sunday found the body of a young 
Latino man alongside the Antelope Valley Freeway in Santa Clarita, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The deputy found the unidentified man, believed to have been about 30, at 12:15 
p.m. near the southbound Placerita Canyon Road exit, Sgt. Bruce Sonnenblick 
said. The victim appeared to have suffered puncture wounds to his chest, but it 
was unclear what kind of object caused the wounds, Sonnenblick said. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy will be performed this week to determine the cause of death, he 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
