<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A summary of Southern California-related business litigation developments 
during the week of Dec. 18. 
</P>
<P>
Movie Company Granted Restraining Order: Delta Unique Media Inc. was granted a 
temporary restraining order Tuesday in Los Angeles Superior Court to block 
First Cinema Venture Inc. from distributing the company's adult films, 
including "Naughty Nymphs," "The Sinful Bed" and "Sorry, Wrong Bedroom." Judge 
Warren Deering ruled that First Cinema had distributed Delta Unique films 
without the company's permission. The company, operated by a former Delta 
Unique employee, was ordered not to make any more distribution deals for Delta 
Unique films. No attorney for First Cinema appeared at the hearing, and the 
Santa Monica company could not be reached for comment. (Filed Dec. 19, 1989, 
Case No. C747008) 
