<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL IN BRIEF: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
FOUR ARE INJURED IN PILEUP AT OFF-RAMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Compiled from staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four people were injured early Sunday when a car crashed into an overheated car 
being pushed by three men along a freeway off-ramp. A spokeswoman for the 
California Highway Patrol said a car driven by Young Ko, 41, of Irvine struck 
the disabled car about 1:20 a.m. on the Culver Drive off-ramp from the 
southbound lanes of the Santa Ana Freeway. Ko apparently did not see the 
vehicle as it was being pushed from the side and rear by Salvador S. Figueroa, 
32, of San Gabriel; Carlos Ramos, 21, also of San Gabriel; and a young man CHP 
officers have not yet identified. Figueroa, who suffered broken bones and 
internal injuries, was listed in satisfactory condition at Fountain Valley 
Regional Hospital and Medical Center. Ramos is in fair condition with similar 
injuries. Ko is in stable condition at Western Medical Center-Santa Ana. The 
unidentified man was taken to Humana Hospital-Huntington Beach, where he 
remains in stable condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
